features: ULTRA NON STICK & SCRATCH RESISTANT COATING - The elegantly designed granite interior of this 10 inch stone earth frying pan is ultra non stick and scratch resistant that enhances both durability and cooking performance. Food slides right off the truly nonstick surface for optimum cooking. No chipping, no peeling or flaking. Ideal for use over low to medium heat with minimum oil or butter for healthy diet. Cleans easily.

HEATS QUICKLY & EVENLY - Made of professional grade aluminum alloy that conducts heat quickly and evenly with precise temperature control and no hot spot. Anti-Warp base of the granite frying pan provides outstanding warp resistance and even heat distribution. This nonstick frying pans is designed for professional multiple cooking use and allows you fry up your favorite breakfast, eggs, veggies, meats and more with less oil for healthy diet.

CONVENIENTLY DESIGNED LID & ERGONOMIC HANDLE - Heat resistant glass lid of the stone skillet with lid makes viewing food easy from start to finish. It seals in the flavor and nutrients for a healthier and better tasting food. The nonstick omelet pan stone is specially designed with a long stainless steel handle that is nice to grip, easy to maneuver, and stays cool while cooking. The hanging loop of this nonstick fry pans is for convenient for storage.

INDUCTION COMPATIBLE - This frying pan is made with a flat bottom which allows it to be placed evenly over heat source and suitable for use on all stove tops including induction, glass & gas. Oven safe up to 450°F.
PTFA, PFOA, lead and cadmium free, ideal for healthy cooking. Choose Michelangelo Stone Frying Pan for greener and safer cooking. Package Includes: 1 x 10 Inch Frying Pan with Lid

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing non-stick, but a bump in the middle.
reviews.reviewText: Before this I owned a commercial quality 12" teflon pan I purchased for $22 about 5 years ago. It was my favorite pan and I used it often. When it finally started sticking, I decided to replace it with this "non-toxic" alternative. The new pans weighs about half, so is easier to handle. It is amazing slippery and easy to clean. But it has a bump in the middle so oil and other liquids run to the sides, for which I deducted a star.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect little pan for eggs.
reviews.reviewText: This sweet little pan is perfect for frying, scrambling or poaching eggs. Nothing sticks, so no broken yolks ever! I love it. Bought it to replace a very old frying pan.... Should have done so years ago. I highly recommend this Michelangelo brand. Very well made, Quality is top notch.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I was a little skeptical when I purchased it…. But now I’m a happy cook. Lightweights, no sticking and easy to clean! Recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Looks good.. stay tuned..update
reviews.reviewText: I've just gotten these.. can't give them an honest rating right now because I've only used the smaller one once and not used the bigger one yet at all.. I love the lids. The pans are much lighter than I thought they would be. hope that doesn't mean food will burn easier or pans will not hold a steady heat..... this is why I say , stay tuned.. I'll come back after using them a week or so and add to this.Ok I've used them, washed them etc. I love the pans. Nothing sticks and super easy to clean. I dont like the handles. They get hot. The knobs on the lids were loose. I had to use a screwdriver to tighten then. And those knobs get really hot. Well I forgot to come back in a week or 2 it has now been one year since I purchased these and they are still exactly like new I use them everyday. These are the easiest pens to wash I've ever had and I am 83 years old almost 84. I simply love them. The only thing I've had a problem with is the handles handles on the lids well the knobs UPS are loose And though we tighten them regularly they still come loose but so far no accidents just have to use a plot holder to take the lid off with because of them being so hot

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this pan!
reviews.reviewText: Cooks nicely and no issues with food sticking like the pan before. Great transaction!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Pan I've Owned
reviews.reviewText: I'm not sure why there aren't more great reviews about this pan. I've only owned it for a month now and it hasn't let me down once. I think if you follow the instructions never cooking higher than medium heat which all non-stick pans call for this pan works great. At first I cooked an egg without any oil and just like the commercials it slid right off the pan. Clean up has been a breeze always allowing the pan to return to room temp before washing. With a very little amount of oil every egg and omelette I've cooked never came close to sticking. I am using an induction cooktop so I'm not sure how it would perform on electric and gas. I do think if the rules are followed this pan will always perform great. I'm writing this 9/5/23 so durability still may be a question.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars my pancakes flip and slide easily
reviews.reviewText: Nonstick surface has worked every time so far. I threw out all my Teflon a few years ago and have been using stainless steel. But there were a few things that kept sticking to my stainless. I've been using this pan for about a week now and I've tried some of the recipes that were the most difficult on stainless. So far, everything slides right out of this pan effortlessly. I expect my stainless pans will last 50 years. I am hoping this stone wear pan will serve for a few years. If it lasts longer than that, then I will be impressed. So, the trade off is convenience versus the need to replace a pan that will probably wear out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Surface only lasts a year, or less, then it degrades. But looks & cooks great. Cleans easily.
reviews.reviewText: In March 2021, I bought the 3 pan set + an extra 8". In January 2023 I bought a 3rd 8". With daily use the surface degrades very quickly. (I always use the lowest heat setting and I've NEVER put them in the Dishwasher.) I had to discard one 8" already, and the other 2 are well on their way to a degraded surface.When they start to look bad, I get rid of them.I worry that bits of surface material will end up in my food.The larger pans are used less, so they last longer, but even they show signs of decline.I'm debating whether I want to buy more of these, or look elsewhere for a more durable pan.

reviews.reviewTitle: Best frying pan I used in my life!
reviews.reviewText: WOW, this is the best frying pan I've owned. The material has no coating, so it will last forever like the old cast iron pans. Nothing sticks in it. I don't even need to rinse it, usually I just pour the contents and nothing stays at the bottom. I recommend to anyone who can afford it. I definitely buy another format.

reviews.reviewTitle: they heat fast so watch the heat while cooking
reviews.reviewText: They are the smaller set to go with the large one we have.
